author: LYNSI BURTON, SEATTLEPI.COM STAFF
title: Woman attacked in Seward Park
text:
A woman told police she was attacked by a man while jogging in Seward Park Thursday night.
The woman reported she was running on the upper trail at the park about 5:45 p.m. when a man hit her in the back of the head and pinned her to the ground, according to Seattle police.
She fought off the attacker, but she believes he ran away after another female jogger on the trail, reports say.
The woman described the assailant as 5-feet-6-inches tall, slim build with brown hair. He wore blue jeans and a black hoodie.
Responding police were unable to find the suspect.
Police ask anyone with information about the attack or the suspect to call 911.
